# Cursor rules for this repo (LLM baremetal)
# Keep this file ASCII-only.

## Mission
Build a minimal x86_64 UEFI bare-metal REPL with an OO subsystem. Priority order:
1) Boot stability + reproducible QEMU harness
2) Surgical code changes (easy to review/revert)
3) Minimal repo / no large artifacts committed

## Hard constraints (do not violate)
- Target: x86_64 UEFI (GNU-EFI). No OS calls.
- No libc usage in the UEFI core (avoid stdio/stdlib/malloc unless already used by existing code).
- ASCII only in core code + scripts + docs.
- No model weights in git: do not add/commit .bin/.gguf or disk images.
- Prefer tcg in QEMU for reliability (WHPX can be flaky).

## Repo rules (important)
- Zero bloat: every line must justify itself.
- Minimal diffs: avoid renames and large refactors unless requested.
- Do not touch Karpathy-style files in llama2.c unless explicitly asked.
- Do not hardcode new paths; keep Windows + WSL workflows working.

## Testing rules (always)
- Prefer autorun-based tests; do not rely on interactive typing.
- For no-model iteration, use the autorun harness:
	- Root: ./test-qemu-autorun.ps1
	- Under llm-baremetal/: ./test-qemu-autorun.ps1
- Default: -Accel tcg

## Current expected quick checks
- Fast no-model smoke (OO + journaling):
	pwsh -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\test-qemu-autorun.ps1 -Accel tcg

## If you change behavior
- If you modify llm-baremetal/llama2_efi_final.c, rerun the autorun test.
- If you modify build scripts (build.ps1, create-boot-*.sh), call it out explicitly.

## Implementation style
- Prefer best-effort helpers already in the codebase.
- Avoid new global state unless required.
- Keep logs stable: avoid making tests depend on fragile wording.

## Cursor prompt templates (copy/paste)

### 1) Make a small change safely
"Make a surgical change. Use minimal diff. Keep ASCII-only. After changes, run: pwsh -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\test-qemu-autorun.ps1 -Accel tcg. If it fails, inspect the serial log path printed by the harness."

### 2) Debug a failing boot/test
"Diagnose why the autorun test fails. Read the serial log tail first, find the blocking point (model picker, prompt, autorun EOF, shutdown), then propose the smallest fix. Do not add new features."

### 3) Repo hygiene reminder
"Do not add/commit model weights (.bin/.gguf) or disk images. If needed, add to .gitignore and use download scripts + checksums instead."

### 4) OO system only (no model)
"Work ONLY on the OO subsystem and related persistence/journaling. Do not modify inference, GGUF, tokenizer, or model loading logic. Keep the repo no-model friendly. Validate using the autorun no-model harness: pwsh -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\\test-qemu-autorun.ps1 -Accel tcg."

## How to use Cursor effectively (recommended workflow)
1) Ask Cursor to make ONE change at a time.
2) Always ask it to run the autorun harness right after.
3) When debugging, provide the serial log tail (last ~120 lines) only.